				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/eric-h" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(474585); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=474585&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610164601" alt="eric_h" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=474585)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/eric-h" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(474585); return false;" >eric_h</a></span> <span class="odate time_1336876334 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">13 May 2012 02:32</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1447040">
									

<p>I'm not going to say you're wrong, since originally I had this up as a regular SCP. My rationale was that the technology is a bit off; I'm 99.9999% sure it's not actually possible to make one of these things, and have it work as described. But a bunch of folks commented it would be better as an -EX, I assume because the effects are completely explained by technology, and the tech doesn't sound all that futuristic.</p>
<p>It's in the grey area of sounding like a real thing someone could make, but it actually isn't.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;If&nbsp;you&nbsp;really&nbsp;want&nbsp;to&nbsp;know&nbsp;why&nbsp;this&nbsp;thing&nbsp;is&nbsp;bogus,&nbsp;click&nbsp;here...</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;OK,&nbsp;can&nbsp;we&nbsp;hide&nbsp;that,&nbsp;now&nbsp;that&nbsp;my&nbsp;suspension&nbsp;of&nbsp;disbelief&nbsp;is&nbsp;completely&nbsp;trashed?</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>OK, I assumed a ton of things are possible here, and most of them aren't:</p>
<ul>
<li>Dr. Bright is correct that an audio transmitter probably won't fit into a normal-sized d20.</li>
<li>I don't think there is really an analog of DMSO that is solid at room temperature.</li>
<li>You probably can't mix DMSO with plastic and still have plastic.</li>
<li>Mixing DMSO with hallucinogens probably doesn't really work to make you trip via skin contact &#8212; although there are rumors to the contrary: Look up Lysergic Acid Crypto-Ethylene on the Web and decide for yourself.</li>
<li>Psychoacoustics seems to be a somewhat dodgy area of science and I'm pretty sure you can't hypnotize someone with some weird combination of sounds.</li>
<li>Even if all the stuff above worked, I don't think the effect would be that consistent.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>

